About 28 billion cubic meters (Bcm) of new gas find and 60 million barrels of condensate will largely be channelled to the domestic market in order to feed the power sector. This comes two months after the announcement of a significant gas and condensate find in the deeper sequences of the Obiafu-Obrikom fields, in oil mining lease (OML) 61, onshore Niger Delta, by oil major Eni, at the Obiafu-41 discovery just three weeks after well completion.
